Ivory Coast Crude Oil Exports From Abidjan Surge, Cotton Falls

-- B y   O l i v i e r   M o n n i e r   a n d   B a u d e l a i r e   M i e u
-- 
2011-07-18T16:14:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-18/ivory-coast-crude-oil-exports-from-abidjan-surge-cotton-falls.html
Exports of crude oil from  Ivory
Coast ’s port at Abidjan, the commercial capital, soared nearly
ninefold in May, according to data from the harbor.  Shipments increased to 89,380 metric tons, from 10,030 tons
in the same period a year earlier, according to the data, which
was distributed to Bloomberg News in the city today.  Cotton exports declined to 12,060 tons, compared with
33,500 tons last year, the port’s data showed. Shipments of
manganese fell to 803 tons from 7,132 tons a year earlier while
cashew-nut exports dropped 58 percent to 48,082 tons, according
to the port’s data.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Olivier Monnier and Baudelaire Mieu in Abidjan via Accra at
   ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 